				<p><p>To answer your questions directly, the X-shape is not the only design that will work.  There are many variations of frame design around a number of rotors that can range from 3 to (in some cases) 8.  </p>

<p><a href="http://www.personal-drones.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/SFC4410_ASSEMBLED.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/E5iCNm.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>

<p>Since it hasn't been mentioned in the other answers, I want to point out that perhaps the biggest reason for the X shape is to keep the weight in the center, <a href="https://robotics.stackexchange.com/a/251/350">which decreases the moment of inertia of the vehicle</a> -- the vehicle will pitch and roll more easily in response to the thrust.</p>
</p><br>
			</div>
