				<p><p>Any frame design that:</p>

<ul>
<li>Is not too heavy</li>
<li>Does not flex too much</li>
<li>keeps the motors the same distance apart when measured diagonally(to use default x or + motor layouts)</li>
<li>can fit all required equipment</li>
<li>allows the flight controller board to be mounted in the centre</li>
</ul>

<p>There are many other frame designs like the V-tail or dead cat that require you to use different motor mix settings.</p>

<p>Also you may want to look into H frame designs, they are relatively simple, and easy to repair.</p>
